- I have no idea but they were valued to him.

7
00:01:50,051 --> 00:01:53,051
Kirk to shuttle 1, both
of us is out of the kill zone.

8
00:01:53,064 --> 00:01:54,164
Your are clear, repeat...

9
00:01:54,213 --> 00:01:58,513
Spock, get in there and neutralize
the volcano let's get out of here.

10
00:02:04,532 --> 00:02:06,532
We have do this now!

11
00:02:06,567 --> 00:02:09,667
I told the Captain, the shuttle
was not built to this kind of heat.

12
00:02:09,723 --> 00:02:12,023
Captain, did any one
indigenous life forms see you.

13
00:02:12,026 --> 00:02:13,626
No, Mr. Spock they did not.

14
00:02:13,665 --> 00:02:16,365
The prime directive clearly states
that there cannot be no interference,

15
00:02:16,381 --> 00:02:18,381
with the internal development
of alien civilizations.

16
00:02:18,465 --> 00:02:22,135
I know what it says which is why
I'm running through jungle, wearing a disguise.

17
00:02:22,155 --> 00:02:25,165
Now, drop off your
super ice-cube, and let's go!

18
00:02:25,604 --> 00:02:27,324
- Kirk out.
- You are good.

19
00:02:27,407 --> 00:02:29,807
If we are going to do this,
we got to do it now.

20
00:02:30,111 --> 00:02:32,111
Ash is killing our coils.

21
00:02:32,144 --> 00:02:33,884
Are you sure you don't
want me go instead.

22
00:02:33,890 --> 00:02:36,422
That would be highly illogical as I'm
already outfitted in heat resistance...

23
00:02:36,425 --> 00:02:38,175
Spock, I was kidding.

24
00:02:39,046 --> 00:02:42,246
- You got this.
- Guys, we have to go, now!

25
00:02:51,225 --> 00:02:53,295
They are trying to kill us!

26
00:02:53,686 --> 00:02:55,601
They are trying to kill us!

27
00:02:55,636 --> 00:02:57,998
I'll see you in 90 seconds.

28
00:03:02,572 --> 00:03:04,372
Do it... do it!

29
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,373
H-two, seven, three...

30
00:03:25,297 --> 00:03:28,051
I can't hold this position,
Spock, I'll got to pull you back up!

31
00:03:28,070 --> 00:03:31,051
Negative. This is our only
chance to save the species.

32
00:03:31,052 --> 00:03:33,302
If this volcano erupts,
the planet dies.

33
00:03:35,186 --> 00:03:37,727
Pull back up! Now!

34
00:03:51,207 --> 00:03:53,450
Spock, are you okay?

35
00:03:59,953 --> 00:04:04,294
I'm surprisingly, alive.
Standby.

36
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:06,398
We have to get him back!
I suit up and go down.

37
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:08,608
- We have to abandon the shuttle.
- We cannot just leave him there.

38
00:04:08,613 --> 00:04:10,686
We don't have a choice.
Uhura, I'm sorry.

39
00:04:11,222 --> 00:04:13,864
Spock, we are going back to the Enterprise.
We get you out of there.

40
00:04:13,895 --> 00:04:16,212
Captain, I'm ditching the shuttle.

41
00:04:16,213 --> 00:04:18,763
- You must make it to Enterprise
on your own. - Wonderful.

42
00:04:19,048 --> 00:04:21,728
- Uhura, are you ready to swim?
- I'm ready.

43
00:04:25,598 --> 00:04:28,382
Jim, the beach
is that way.

44
00:04:28,732 --> 00:04:30,484
I know, we don't
going to the beach!

45
00:04:30,802 --> 00:04:32,520
Oh, no, no!

46
00:04:36,850 --> 00:04:38,460
I hate this!

47
00:04:38,860 --> 00:04:40,645
I know you do!

48
00:05:23,012 --> 00:05:26,688
Do you have any idea, how ridiculous is
to hide a starship on the bottom of the ocean.

49
00:05:26,689 --> 00:05:28,843
We've been doing this since last night.
The salt-water is going to erodes...

50
00:05:28,944 --> 00:05:31,174
Scotty! Where is Spock?

51
00:05:31,283 --> 00:05:33,340
Still in the volcano, sir.

52
00:06:13,990 --> 00:06:15,089
Captain on the bridge!

53
00:06:15,889 --> 00:06:18,524
Lieutenant, do we have
an open channel for Mr. Spock?

54
00:06:18,530 --> 00:06:20,856
The heat is frying his comms
but we still have a contact.

55
00:06:22,846 --> 00:06:24,238
Spock!

56
00:06:24,308 --> 00:06:26,283
I activated the device, Captain.

57
00:06:26,354 --> 00:06:29,311
When the countdown is complete
the reaction should render the volcano inert.

58
00:06:29,321 --> 00:06:31,000
Yeah, that's going
to render him inert.

59
00:06:31,004 --> 00:06:32,782
- Should we have use of the transporters?
- Negative, sir.

60
00:06:32,785 --> 00:06:35,480
- Not with this kind of magnetic field...
- I need to beam Spock back to the ship.

61
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:36,845
Give me one way to do it.

62
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:39,718
Maybe if we have
direct line of sight...

63
00:06:39,730 --> 00:06:42,190
No way. You are talking
about an active volcano.

64
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:45,500
Sir, if that thing erupts, I can't guarantee
that will withstand the heat.

65
00:06:45,510 --> 00:06:47,400
I do not know if we can maintain
that kind of altitude.

66
00:06:47,410 --> 00:06:50,679
Our shuttle was concealed by the ash cloud,
but the Enterprise is too large.

67
00:06:51,065 --> 00:06:54,200
If utilized in a rescue effort,
it would be revealed to the indigenous species.

68
00:06:54,230 --> 00:06:57,951
Spock, nobody knows the rules better than you,
but there got to be an exception.

69
00:06:57,998 --> 00:07:00,694
Non. Such action
violates prime directive.

70
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:02,810
Shut up, Spock!
We are trying to save you, damn it!

71
00:07:02,814 --> 00:07:05,654
Doctor, the needs of the many
out weight needs of the few.

72
00:07:05,676 --> 00:07:07,309
Spock we are
talking about your life.

73
00:07:07,441 --> 00:07:09,820
The rule cannot be
violated in any case...

74
00:07:10,021 --> 00:07:11,421
Spock!

75
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,379
Try to get him back on-line.

76
00:07:13,405 --> 00:07:15,253
90 seconds to detonation.

77
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:20,419
If Spock were here
and I was there, what would he do?

78
00:07:23,469 --> 00:07:25,207
He lets you die.

79
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:08,508
Spock!

80
00:09:08,973 --> 00:09:10,326
You are all-right?

81
00:09:10,422 --> 00:09:12,700
Captain, you let them
see our ship.

82
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,141
He is fine.

83
00:09:14,186 --> 00:09:16,267
- Bridge to Captain Kirk.
- Yes, Lieutenant.

84
00:09:16,393 --> 00:09:19,893
- Is Commander Spock on board, sir?
- Safely and sound.

85
00:09:19,924 --> 00:09:22,994
Please notify him that,
the device successfully detonated.

86
00:09:23,688 --> 00:09:26,031
<i>You heard that?
Congratulations, Spock!</i>

87
00:09:26,736 --> 00:09:28,230
You just saved the world.

88
00:09:28,231 --> 00:09:32,902
