00:12:13,862 --> 00:12:15,502
What did you say?

92
00:12:15,575 --> 00:12:17,284
Your daughter.

93
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:20,140
I can save her.

94
00:12:20,944 --> 00:12:22,731
Who are you?

95
00:12:41,056 --> 00:12:43,991
Jim, come on,
Let it go.

96
00:12:45,014 --> 00:12:47,919
You are not actually
answer that, are you?

97
00:12:48,102 --> 00:12:49,762
San Francisco,
Starfleet Headquarters

98
00:12:49,764 --> 00:12:52,299
Spock, I'm telling you
this why he called, I can feel it.

99
00:12:52,941 --> 00:12:55,200
Your feelings aside,
I consider highly unlikely,

100
00:12:55,201 --> 00:12:57,936
we will be selected
for the new program.

101
00:12:58,100 --> 00:13:00,272
Why else would Pike
want to see us?

102
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:03,404
Forget about seniority, they gave
us the newest ship in the fleet.

103
00:13:03,405 --> 00:13:05,849
- And who else they going to send out.
- I can think numerous the possibilities...

104
00:13:05,850 --> 00:13:07,476
A five-year mission, Spock.

105
00:13:07,518 --> 00:13:11,287
That's deep space, that's uncharted
territories, think incredible that's going to be.

106
00:13:11,508 --> 00:13:13,574
Hello, ladies!
Jim Kirk.

107
00:13:15,091 --> 00:13:17,111
- Uneventful.
- Admiral?

108
00:13:17,225 --> 00:13:19,853
That's the way you describe
the survey in Nibiru in Captain's log.

109
00:13:19,854 --> 00:13:22,213
Yes sir, I didn't want to waste your time
going with the details.

110
00:13:22,214 --> 00:13:24,053
Tell me more about this volcano.

111
00:13:24,091 --> 00:13:27,401
Data says was highly volatile. If it would
be erupt, it would wipe out the planet?

112
00:13:27,402 --> 00:13:30,762
- Let's hope it doesn't, sir.
- Something tells me it won’t.

113
00:13:31,157 --> 00:13:34,532
Well sir, volatile is all relative.
Maybe our... data was off.

114
00:13:34,757 --> 00:13:39,150
Or maybe it didn't erupted, because Mr. Spock
detonated a cold fusion device inside it,

115
00:13:39,232 --> 00:13:43,387
right after a civilization that's
barely invented the wheel,

116
00:13:43,388 --> 00:13:46,336
happen to see a starship
rising out their ocean.

117
00:13:46,494 --> 00:13:48,954
That's pretty much how
you describe it, is it not?

118
00:13:48,955 --> 00:13:51,945
- Admiral... - You filed a report?
Why did you not tell me?

119
00:13:51,950 --> 00:13:54,550
I correctly assumed that you would
be truthful in your Captain's log.

120
00:13:54,551 --> 00:13:56,490
Yeah, I'd would been
if I didn't have to save your life.

121
00:13:56,491 --> 00:13:58,187
A fact for which I'm
deeply grateful

122
00:13:58,188 --> 00:14:01,521
and very reason I felt necessary to take
responsibility for the actions taken by...

123
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:05,499
Oh, yeah don't be so noble pointy
if you also throwing me under the bus.

124
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:08,397
- Pointy? Is that a derogative
reference? - Gentlemen.

125
00:14:09,221 --> 00:14:12,787
Starfleet's mandate is to explore-
and to observe, not to interfere.

126
00:14:12,788 --> 00:14:15,019
Had the mission had
gone as planned, admiral,

127
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:17,331
Indigenous species would be never
been aware of our interference.

128
00:14:17,332 --> 00:14:19,597
- That's a technicality.
- I am Vulcan, sir.

129
00:14:19,598 --> 00:14:21,645
- We in-praise technicality.
- You giving me attitude, Spock.

130
00:14:21,646 --> 00:14:24,209
I'm expressing multiple attitudes
simultaneous, sir.

131
00:14:24,293 --> 00:14:26,667
- To which you are referring to?
- Out.

132
00:14:27,475 --> 00:14:29,491
You're dismissed, Commander.

133
00:14:37,983 --> 00:14:43,082
- Do you have any idea what
a pain in the ass, you are? - I think so, sir.

134
00:14:43,085 --> 00:14:46,569
So, tell me what did you wrong?
What's the lesson to be learned here?

135
00:14:46,947 --> 00:14:49,577
- Never trust a Vulcan. - I see,
you cant even answer the question.

136
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:52,158
You lied on a, official report,
you lied.

137
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:54,980
You think the rules don't apply to you
because you disagree with them?

138
00:14:55,017 --> 00:14:57,979
That's why you talk me into signing up in first place.
That's why you gave me your ship.

139
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,931
I gave you my ship because
I saw a greatness in you...

140
00:15:02,525 --> 00:15:04,864
And now I see you don't
have got ounce of humility.

141
00:15:04,865 --> 00:15:07,500
- What I suppose to do? Let Spock die?
- You are missing the point.

142
00:15:07,501 --> 00:15:09,233
I don't think I'm, sir.
What would you have done?

143
00:15:09,254 --> 00:15:12,823
I would not risked my first officers
life in the first place.

144
00:15:12,842 --> 00:15:16,450
You suppose to survey a planet
not alter its destiny.

145
00:15:16,455 --> 00:15:20,850
You violated dozens starfleet regulations and
almost got everyone under your command killed.

146
00:15:20,861 --> 00:15:23,658
But except I didn't, you know
how many crew have I lost since...

147
00:15:23,669 --> 00:15:25,423
- That's your problem! - Since I took command?
- This and the defect is.

148
00:15:25,424 --> 00:15:27,380
- You think you're infallible. - Not one.
- You think not you can't make mistakes,

149
00:15:27,381 --> 00:15:29,019
It's a pattern with you.

150
00:15:29,043 --> 00:15:31,386
- That the rules are for the other people.
- Some should be.

151
00:15:31,387 --> 00:15:35,402
And what's worse is you using
plain luck to justify, you playing God!

152
00:15:38,497 --> 00:15:41,567
Given the circumstances, this has been
brought to admiral Marcus attention.

153
00:15:41,568 --> 00:15:44,836
He convened a special tribunal
to which I was not invited.

154
00:15:44,837 --> 00:15:49,254
You understand what's starfleet
regulations mandate be done in this point?

155
00:15:52,444 --> 00:15:54,588
They taken Enterprise
away from you...

156
00:15:55,488 --> 00:15:57,630
They are sending you
back to the academy.

157
00:16:02,697 --> 00:16:04,148
Admiral, listen.

158
00:16:04,149 --> 00:16:06,165
No, why should I listen?

159
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:09,106
You don't listen anybody but yourself!
Every decision I've made...

160
00:16:09,111 --> 00:16:10,727
I can't listen.

161
00:16:10,728 --> 00:16:14,304
You don't comply with the rules,
you don't take responsibility for anything,

162
00:16:14,305 --> 00:16:16,816
and you don't respect the chair.

163
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:20,655
You know why?

164
00:16:20,855 --> 00:16:23,459
Because you're not ready for it.

165
00:16:37,651 --> 00:16:41,669
LONDON

166
00:18:49,669 --> 00:18:51,921
Transmission sent
to: admiral Marcus

167
00:19:45,228 --> 00:19:48,366
- How did you find me?
- I know you better than you I think you do.

168
00:19:50,727 --> 00:19:53,428
When I first time found you
was in a dive-bar like this.

169
00:19:54,253 --> 00:19:56,850
Remember that? Got your ass
handed to you.

170
00:19:57,710 --> 00:19:59,341
- No it didn't.
- You don't?

171
00:19:59,342 --> 00:20:01,871
- No, it wasn't what happen...
- That was an epic beating.

172
00:20:01,875 --> 00:20:03,213
No, it wasn't.

173
00:20:03,215 --> 00:20:06,926
You had napkins hanging
out of your nose... did you not?

174
00:20:08,780 --> 00:20:11,296
Yeah, that was a good fight.

175
00:20:11,718 --> 00:20:13,387
A good fight?

176
00:20:16,335 --> 00:20:19,107
I think that's your problem
right there.

177
00:20:23,486 --> 00:20:25,491
They gave it back to me.

178
00:20:26,338 --> 00:20:28,358
The Enterprise.

179
00:20:39,698 --> 00:20:41,425
Congratulations!

180
00:20:43,874 --> 00:20:46,127
Watch your back with
that first officer, thou.

181
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:50,497
Spock not going to work
with me, he is been transferred.

182
00:20:51,228 --> 00:20:53,295
USS Bradbury.

183
00:20:55,705 --> 00:20:57,747
You are going to be
my first officer.

184
00:20:58,361 --> 00:21:00,608
Yeah, Marcus took
some convincing...

185
00:21:02,486 --> 00:21:05,046
But any now and then
I can make a good case.

186
00:21:08,492 --> 00:21:11,961
- What did you tell him?
- The truth...

187
00:21:12,670 --> 00:21:14,870
That I believe in you.

188
00:21:15,670 --> 00:21:19,517
And if anybody deserves
a second chance, it's Jim Kirk.

189
00:21:29,759 --> 00:21:31,826
I don't know what to say.

190
00:21:32,220 --> 00:21:33,962
That is a first.

191
00:21:35,309 --> 00:21:37,527
It's going to be okay, son.

192
00:21:44,780 --> 00:21:47,016
An emergency session
at the Daystrom.

193
00:21:47,977 --> 00:21:50,410
- That's us.
- Yeah.

194
00:21:51,693 --> 00:21:53,406
Suit up.

195
00:22:09,269 --> 00:22:12,652
- Captain. - Not any more,
Spock, first officer.

196
00:22:14,204 --> 00:22:16,580
I was demoted
and you were resigned.

197
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:19,341
It's fortunate that the consequences
were not more severe.

198
00:22:19,420 --> 00:22:20,889
You gotta be kidding me!

199
00:22:20,950 --> 00:22:23,319
- Captain, my intention was not...
- Not Captain.

200
00:22:23,684 --> 00:22:26,890
I saved your life Spock. You
wrote a report, I lost my ship.

201
00:22:28,905 --> 00:22:33,058
Commander, I see now I should
alerted to the fact I submitted the report.

202
00:22:33,508 --> 00:22:37,681
Now I'm, familiar with your compulsion to follow
the rules, but, see I cant do that.

203
00:22:38,428 --> 00:22:42,016
Where I come from, if someone saves
your life you don't stab him at the back.

204
00:22:42,029 --> 00:22:43,663
Vulcan's cannot lie.

205
00:22:43,674 --> 00:22:45,928
Then I'm talking to
the half-human part of you.

206
00:22:45,963 --> 00:22:49,992
Do you understand
why I went back for you?

207
00:22:50,033 --> 00:22:53,359
Commander Spock?
I'm Frank Abbott, USS Bradbury.

208
00:22:53,679 --> 00:22:55,699
Guess you are with me.

209
00:22:56,761 --> 00:22:58,574
Yes, Captain.

210
00:23:06,809 --> 00:23:08,871
The truth is
I'm going to miss you.

211
00:23:16,480 --> 00:23:18,873
<i>Admiral Marcus, sir.</i>

212
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:22,517
Thank you for meeting
on such short notice.

213
00:23:22,987 --> 00:23:24,723
Be seated.

214
00:23:26,422 --> 00:23:28,965
By now some of you heard
what happened in London.

215
00:23:29,511 --> 00:23:33,175
The target was a starfleet data archive,
now it's a damn hole in the ground.

216
00:23:33,180 --> 00:23:35,145
42 men and women are dead.

217
00:23:35,501 --> 00:23:38,148
One hour ago, I received a message
from starfleet officer,

218
00:23:38,175 --> 00:23:40,557
who confessed to
carrying out this attack.

219
00:23:40,581 --> 00:23:44,566
That he been forced to do this by this man,
Commander John Harrison.

220
00:23:44,808 --> 00:23:49,119
He's one of of our own and he's the man
responsibility this act of savagery.

221
00:23:49,421 --> 00:23:53,822
For reasons unknown, John Harrison has just
declared one man war against starfleet.

222
00:23:54,891 --> 00:23:59,172
Under no circumstances are we to allowed
this man to escape Federation space.

223
00:24:00,019 --> 00:24:04,110
You here tonight represent the senior
command of all the vessels in the region.

224
00:24:04,121 --> 00:24:06,357
And in the name of those
that we lost...

225
00:24:06,766 --> 00:24:09,277
You will run this bastard down.

226
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:13,193
This is a manhunt, pure and
simple so let's get to work.

227
00:24:13,759 --> 00:24:17,318
Earth perimeter sensors hasn't detected
any warp signatures leaving the system,

228
00:24:17,320 --> 00:24:19,559
so we know he cannot be far.

229
00:24:20,030 --> 00:24:22,091
You park ships at
blockade formation,

230
00:24:22,092 --> 00:24:24,497
and deploy search vehicles
and landing parties,

231
00:24:24,544 --> 00:24:26,544
to run down every lead.

232
00:24:26,765 --> 00:24:29,998
This man has shown willingness
to kill innocent people...

233
00:24:30,005 --> 00:24:33,561
so rules of engagement are simple
if you come across this man

